Hormel Foods Corporation is an American food company based in Austin, Minnesota. The company was founded as George A. Hormel & Company in Austin by George A. Hormel in 1891. It changed its name to Hormel Foods in 1993.
Hormel sells food under many brands, including the Applegate, Chi-Chi's, Dinty Moore, Farmer John, Herdez, Jennie-O, Justin's, Lloyd's, Muscle Milk, Skippy, Spam, Stagg, La Victoria[6] and Wholly Guacamole brands, as well as under its own name.[7] The company is listed on the Fortune 500.



