Jeffrey M. Ettinger: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 1:02 AM ET
Food Products

Company Overview of Hormel Foods Corporation



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Jeffrey M. Ettinger  Chairman of the Board, Hormel Foods CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships59$12,192,836As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Jeffrey M. Ettinger, also known as Jeff, served as the Chief Executive Officer of Hormel Foods Corporation from January 2006 to October 30, 2016. Mr. Ettinger served as the President of Hormel Foods Corporation from June 28, 2004 to October 25, 2015. He joined Hormel Foods in 1989 as Corporate Attorney. He served as the Chief Operating Officer of Hormel Foods Corp., from June 1, 2004 to December 31, 2005. He served as a Group Vice President of Hormel Foods Corporation ... from April 30, 2001 to March 2, 2003. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Jennie-O Turkey Store, a subsidiary of Hormel Foods Corp., from March 3, 2003 to June 27, 2004. He served as the President and Chief Operating Officer of Jennie-O Turkey Store from April 30, 2001 to March 2, 2003. He served as a Vice President of Hormel from January 31, 2000 to April 29, 2001 and Jennie-O Foods from November 1, 1999 to January 30, 2000. He served as a Treasurer of Hormel from April 27, 1998 to October 31, 1999; Assistant Treasurer from November 24, 1997 to April 26, 1998; Special Assignment from September 8, 1997 to November 23, 1997 and also served as Grocery Products Product Manager from April 10, 1995 to September 7, 1997. Mr. Ettinger also served as Product Manager for Hormel chili products and corporate and senior attorney at Hormel. He has more than 25 years of experience with Hormel Foods. He served as a law clerk for the Honorable Arthur Alarcon, the U.S. Court of Appeals, 9th Circuit. He has been the Chairman and Director at Hormel Foods Corporation since November 21, 2006 and May 2004 respectively. He serves as a Director at North American Meat Institute. He has been an Independent Director of The Toro Company since July 1,2010. He has been an Independent Director of Ecolab Inc. since May 2015 and as its  Independent Lead Director since May 4, 2017. He serves as a member of the board of directors of the Grocery Manufacturers of America Association, the Minnesota Business Partnership, the Austin Medical Center Foundation, The Hormel Institute and The Hormel Foundation. He is the founding chair of the Hormel’s diversity and inclusion council, which aims to meet the growing needs of its diverse workforce and consumer base. He attended the Program for Management Development at Harvard Business School. Mr. Ettinger holds Bachelors and Juris Doctor degrees from the University of California Los Angeles.Read Full Background




